As an addendum to Arnaud's comprehensive description of how to fix your 
brake ills, I would add that you should ALWAYS fix/replace BOTH front or 
BOTH rear brake calipers/pads/shoes/wheel cylinders/hoses/etc at the same 
time, even if only one side is causing problems.


